Differential capacity of left and right hemispheric areas for compensation of poststroke aphasia. As previous functional neuroimaging studies could not settle the controversy regarding the contribution of dominant and subdominant hemisphere to recovery from poststroke aphasia, language performance was related to H2(15)O-positron emission tomographic activation patterns in 23 right-handed aphasic patients 2 and 8 weeks after stroke. In patients classified according to the site of lesion (frontal, n = 7 subcortical, n = 9